body:
@mlissner and I discovered a bug in the court regexes, where for example "Southern District of New York" would match to NDNY ("Northern District of New York"), due to NDNY matching on "N District of New York", case-insensitivity, and the fact that "Southern" ends with "N". This bug has resulted in all WDNY and SDNY judges being assigned to NDNY, for example. 

This bug is likely causing problems in all district courts with "western/southern/northern/etc". We don't know yet whether it has affected Court ID assignments (rather than just judges in the people DB). 

Fixing the bug is just a matter of adding the word boundary character, `\b' at the beginning of all relevant regexes.
